# Guardentra — master project architecture rules

## Backend / Cloud Run / Firebase App Hosting

- Backend configurations must always read the dynamic environment port variable via `process.env.PORT || 8080` and explicitly bind to network host `0.0.0.0`.
- Never hardcode ports 3000 or 5000, as this triggers Firebase App Hosting container startup timeouts.

## Branch architecture

- Establish an isolated branch architecture: `dev` for sandboxing, `test` for staging builds, and `main` for production deployments feeding guardentra.com.

## Firebase environments

- Demo project `guardentra-7f582` is not production. Prefer separate projects: `guardentra-dev`, `guardentra-staging`, `guardentra-prod` (see `docs/ENVIRONMENTS.md` and `.firebaserc`).
- Client may use `VITE_FIREBASE_*` env vars; otherwise falls back to committed demo `firebase-applet-config.json`.
